summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsSustainable PackagingYou don't have to be in your villain era to embrace BADgal beauty. An intense lash that's all volume, no weight? Oh, yeah. With Benefit's BADgal BANG! volumizing mascara, every swipe lays on 360 fullness that lasts 36 hours* without smudging. So if you wanna be a little bad, we're good with that.

reviews.headline: Something is off
reviews.comments: I have used this mascara for years. Lately my eyes have been bothering me, I thought well maybe my tube is old so I threw it out and started a brand new one. Same irritation. Benefits claims it did not change the formula but it is different - it seems wetter which is causing more clumping and it doesn't seem to lift as well as if the formula is too heavy.

media.headline: BEST.. MASCARA.. EVER!!!!!!!
media.caption: The wand is the best part!

faceoff_positive.comments:
I feel like this is my DREAM mascara! I cant believe how well it works! I saw other reviews, with terrible things to say, but for me I feel like its the complete opposite.

Personally, I like very long lashes, separated, sweeping to touch my eyebrows. Naturally my eyelashes are straight, fine, and average length. But a simple curl with a lash curler, and 2 coats of this mascara, I have superstar lashes.

I didn't have any issues with clumping, or drying. My only tiny issue, and this is with every mascara I use, is smudging, I have very oily eyelids & Houston humidity, so when my eyelashes touch my upper lid you see some smudges. HOWEVER, some urban decay shadow primer = no smudges. I urge people to try this mascara for themselves!

The mascara brush is my favorite design, its slender, tapered, and rubber wand and tips are the best design. It combs through from root to tip leaving your entire lash covered and separated.

This mascara is either a love it or hate it. I definitely LOVEEEE it!

Please see the pictures I uploaded just so you have an idea of what the mascara looks like on by itself.
faceoff_positive.headline: BEST.. MASCARA.. EVER!!!!!!!

faceoff_negative.comments: Bought this a couple weeks ago when they were advertising it at the front of the store. Seemed pretty good when I first applied it, definitely lengthened and defined my very thin lashes. But it did smudge a lot by lunch and when I went to remove it that night, nightmare! Would not come off! Flakes everywhere including in my eyes. Gave it a couple more tries, wish I hadn't. Third day I wore it and removed it I ended up at the opthomologist with a scratched eye from the flakes! Never use again! Be warned!
faceoff_negative.headline: Ridiculous
